    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Rectangular ornaments or framing devices that contain an inscription or image, with triangular or semicircular winglike handles on two sides. These appear in a variety of contexts including mosaics, architecture, pottery, amulets, and sculpture, especially dedicatory or funerary inscriptions. They are based on objects of the same shape that were a popular form of Roman votive tablet.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
